T1	Intervention 526 632	randomly allocated to three groups: intraoperative music, postoperative music and silence (control group).
T2	Intervention 633 741	Anaesthesia and postoperative analgesia were standardized and the same surgeon performed all the operations.
T3	Intervention 742 856	Stress response was assessed during and after surgery by determining the plasma cortisol and blood glucose levels.
T4	Intervention 857 929	Immune function was evaluated by studying immunoglobulin A (IgA) levels.
T5	Intervention 930 1064	Patients' postoperative pain, anxiety, blood pressure (BP), heart rate (HR) and oxygen saturation were also studied as stress markers.
